<subSubSection id="C37E65682B69FFA626F1FD28FBD481EF" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDB36E32B69FFA626F1FD28FBD481EF" blockId="13.[151,1437,721,1106]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B69FFA626F1FD28FE9C80E3" bold="true" box="[151,273,721,746]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small bodied specimens, body usually covered by numerous papillae. Palps totally fused or with distal notch. Prostomium with 3 antennae and 2 pairs of eyes, anterior eyespots usually absent. Peristomium with 1 pair of peristomial cirri. Antennae, peristomial and dorsal cirri with similar shape, with bulbous, inflate bases, and narrower, tapering tips. Dorsal cirri usually absent on chaetiger 2. Parapodial glands frequently present, with granular or fibrilar material. Compound chaetae as heterogomph falcigers, usually with short, unidentate blades. Aciculae frequently stout, subdistally bent at ~90°, with acute tips. Pharynx narrow, with opening surrounded by soft, rounded papillae, and conical central tooth at anterior margin; proventricle short, with few, coarse rows of muscle cells. Reproduction by epigamy, with ventral incubation of eggs and embryos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65682B69FFA626A1FC08FDB6865B" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDB36E32B69FFA626A1FC08FDB6865B" blockId="13.[151,1437,721,1106]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B69FFA626A1FC08FEB68603" bold="true" box="[199,315,1009,1034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus currently counts with 2 formal records for the Brazilian coast, 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B69FFA62213FC0BFE278627" authority="Nogueira, San Martin &amp; Fukuda, 2004" authorityName="Nogueira, San Martin &amp; Fukuda" authorityYear="2004" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="annulata">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B69FFA62213FC0BFB7B8603" box="[1141,1270,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">S. annulata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B69FFA6229AFC08FE278627" author="Nogueira" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M., San Martin, G. &amp; Fukuda, M. V. (2004) On some exogonines (Polychaeta, Syllidae, Exogoninae) from the northern coast of the State of Sao Paulo, southeastern Brazil Results of BIOTA / FAPESP / bentos marinho Project. Meiofauna marina, 13, 45 - 77." type="journal article" year="2004">Nogueira, San Martín &amp; Fukuda, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B69FFA62780FBEFFBDE8627" authority="Nogueira, San Martin &amp; Amaral, 2001" authorityName="Nogueira, San Martin &amp; Amaral" authorityYear="2001" box="[486,1107,1045,1070]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B69FFA62780FBEFFD0B8627" box="[486,646,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">S. brasiliensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B69FFA624F6FBECFBDE8627" author="Nogueira" box="[656,1107,1045,1070]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M., San Martin, G. &amp; Amaral, A. C. Z. (2001) Description of five new species of Exogoninae Rioja, 1925 (Polychaeta: Syllidae) associated with the stony coral Mussismilia hispida (Verrill, 1868) in Sao Paulo State, Brazil. Journal of Natural History, 35 (12), 1773 - 1794." type="journal article" year="2001">Nogueira, San Martín &amp; Amaral, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, plus ~8 other species, from informal records (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B69FFA627F1FBC0FDA2865B" author="Fukuda" box="[407,559,1081,1106]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Fukuda, M. V. (2010) Contribuicao ao conhecimento taxonomico dos silideos Polychaeta: Syllidae) da regiao sudeste-sul do Brasil. PhD thesis, Instituto de Biociencias, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 340 pp." type="book" year="2010">Fukuda 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
